{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Japanese Knotweed surveys mandatory when selling property",
        "additional_details": "The UK is a hotspot for Japanese Knotweed. After recently buying my first home, I was devastated to discover it on the property. It\u2019s already cost me over \u00a34,000 to manage, and I\u2019m likely to face a loss in value when I sell. Given how widespread this issue is, I believe surveys that identify Japanese Knotweed should be made mandatory during the sale of a property. I think this would help protect all buyers (especially young, first-time buyers) from unexpected costs and long-term stress.",
        "background": "Make it mandatory for the seller to undertake a survey for Japanese knotweed during the sale of their property.",
